    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.114M69/158.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 245.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In continuation of my despatch No. 243, of
                    today’s date, regarding the trial of the captain of the steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Texas</hi> sunk in Smyrna harbor in April last, I have the
                    honor to transmit herewith copies of two despatches<note n="4" xml:id="d1684fn4"
                        >One of these is the inclosure with Mr. Horton’s No. 45 of July 9,
                        supra.</note> just received by the Embassy from the Consulate General at
                    Smyrna.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                                Smyrna</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                            Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Smyrna</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1912</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                        of your open telegram of this morning<note n="5" xml:id="d1684fn5">Refers to
                            inclosure 2 with Mr. Rockhill’s despatch of July 12, No. 243 sent July 9
                            and received on the 10th.</note> and to inform you that I have
                        immediately sent in a vigorous protest to the local government against the
                        arbitrary and illegal manner in <pb facs="1431" n="1327" xml:id="pg_1327"/>
                        which it is acting in the matter of the captain of the <hi rend="italic"
                            >Texas</hi>, in bringing him to trial on accusations touching the
                        sinking of a ship flying the American flag. I have assured the Governor
                        General that the responsible parties will be called to account for all
                        violations of the provisions of international law and the Capitulations.</p>
                    <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">George Horton</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
